threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

attributes.magic: PE32+ executable (GUI) x86-64, for MS Windows

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This sample is a multifunctional backdoor with SOCKS5 proxy capabilities. Upon execution, it establishes persistence by creating a 'socks5' value in the 'HKCU\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Run' registry key, which points to a hidden PowerShell command to re-launch the malware. It communicates with a Command and Control (C2) server to receive commands, relay network traffic as a SOCKS5 proxy, and download and execute additional malicious payloads. Downloaded files are saved to the Temp directory and executed, and it can also create scheduled tasks for further execution.
